dataIdInfo.idPurp: Massachusetts State Senate 2021 District Boundaries (polygon features), as signed into law on November 4, 2021. These boundaries will be used beginning with the fall 2022 elections.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Massachusetts State Senate 2021 District Boundaries (polygon features), as signed into law on November 4, 2021, with Chapter 82 of the Acts of 2021. These boundaries will be used beginning with the fall 2022 elections and were based on demographic data from the 2020 U.S. Census.

overview.eaover: Senators' names and political party affiliations will be added following the swearing ceremonies based on the certified results of the fall 2022 elections.

prcStep.stepDesc: MassGIS downloaded the polygon data from https://malegislature.gov/Redistricting/NewDistricts/Senate and projected the data to Mass. State Plane NAD 1983 Mainland Meters. MassGIS then incorporated a coastline into the dataset using 2020 TIGER/Line "faces" data downloaded from the U.S. Census Bureau. Distict name and number were calculated based on https://malegislature.gov/assets/redistricting/Senate%20Map%20Key-2021.pdf.
